  ```{r, include=FALSE}
library(MSEtool)
imps <- avail("Imp")
```

MSEtool includes `r length(imps)` example Imp objects. They can be listed using the `avail` function:

  ```{r}
avail('Imp')
```

These objects can be used together with the example [Stock](/object-stock/8-example-stock-objects/_index_en/), [Fleet](/object-fleet/example-objects/_index_en/), and [Obs](/object-obs/example-objects/_index_en/) to quickly create an operating model:

```{r}
OM <- new('OM', Albacore, FlatE_Dom, Generic_Obs, Overages, nsim=100)
````
